sect1.sect2:
cdda &enabled;
This is the Audio CD input. At present, if you are have a new enough libvcdinfo (from vcdimager and a new enough libcdio you will get the newer navigation-capable plugin. Eventually when libcdio is more mature and handles more OSs the older plugin will disapear. The file doc/intf-vcd.txt in the vlc source gives detailed information about this plugin.
Module de lecture de CDs audio.

dvb &disabled;
For GNU/Linux only Seulement pour GNU/Linux
This module allows to read from DVB-S, DVB-T, and DBC-C satellite, digital terrestrial, or cable cards. It uses the Video4Linux 2 API, that is only available in kernel 2.5.X and 2.6.X Ce module permet de lire depuis des cartes DVB-S, DVB-T et DVB-C, de satellite, télévision numérique terrestre ou cable. Il utilise l'API Video4Linux 2, qui n'existe que dans les versions 2.5 et 2.6 du noyau Linux .

pvr &disabled;
For GNU/Linux only Seulement pour GNU/Linux
This module allows to read from Hauppauge PVR cards Ce module permet de lire depuis les cartes Hauppauge PVR .

v4l &disabled;
For GNU/Linux only Seulement pour GNU/Linux
This module allows to get Video4Linux streams Ce module vous permet de lire des flux Video4Linux .

vcd &enabled;
This is the VideoCD input. At present, if you are have a new enough libvcdinfo (from vcdimager and a new enough libcdio you will get the newer navigation-capable plugin. Eventually when libcdio is more mature and handles more OSs the older plugin will disapear. The file doc/intf-vcd.txt in the vlc source gives detailed information about this plugin.
Module de lecture de VideoCD.
